data.enText: protected with a material that prevents heat, sound, electricity, etc. from passing through
data.chText: 有隔热（或隔音、绝缘）保护的

means: 有隔热(或隔音、绝缘)保护的

example.ex: They wonder if their community is no longer insulated from big city problems...
example.tran: 他们在想是否大城市的问题离自己的社区也已经不再遥远了。

example.ex: Their wealth had insulated them from reality.
example.tran: 财富将他们与现实隔离。

value.def: If a person or group is insulated from the rest of society or from outside influences, they are protected from them.
value.tran: 将…隔离(以免受外界影响)

example.ex: They lived in happy insulation from brutal facts.
example.tran: 他们幸福地生活在不受残酷现实干扰的世界里。

example.ex: It will take almost 25 years to insulate the homes of the six million households that require this assistance...
example.tran: 要为 600 万户有此需求的家庭进行住宅隔热隔音处理得花将近 25 年的时间。

example.ex: Is there any way we can insulate our home from the noise?...
example.tran: 有什么办法可以使我们的住宅隔音吗？

example.ex: Are your hot and cold water pipes well insulated?
example.tran: 你们的冷热水管包好隔热层了吗？

example.ex: ...a garment lined with a light insulating material.
example.tran: 里子是轻便保暖材料的衣服

value.def: To insulate something such as a building means to protect it from cold or noise by covering it or surrounding it in a thick layer.

example.ex: In order to make it safe, the element is electrically insulated.
example.tran: 为安全起见,该元件作了电绝缘处理。

value.def: If a piece of equipment is insulated, it is covered with rubber or plastic to prevent electricity passing through it and giving the person using it an electric shock.
